node.text:
A man was arrested after showing up to #ArianaGrande’s house in the middle of the night, and pulled a knife when security tried to get him to leave😳‼️ 

According to TMZ, 23-year-old Aaron Brown's facing a felony brandishing charge for the incident, which our law enforcement sources tell us went down around 2 AM Friday on Ariana's property. 

Brown arrived and demanded to see the singer, and when security told him to beat it ... he refused and pulled a knife. LAPD was called to the scene and arrested him. It's unclear if Ariana was home at the time, but if she was ... she never came out during the altercation or Brown's arrest.

Ariana filed for a temporary restraining order against Brown, and a judge has granted her one until an upcoming hearing.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Rap by RAPTV on September 14, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, beard and text that says 'G-EAZY ARRESTED FOR ASSAULT IN NEW YORK RaP'.

node.text:
#GEazy was arrested for assault in NYC. According to TMZ, G-Eazy was arrested Monday evening and is facing a misdemeanor assault charge ... according to our law enforcement sources.

We're told the rapper's accused of striking the alleged victim in the face, causing pain and redness. He was released after receiving a desk appearance ticket to appear in court at a later date.

Law enforcement sources tell TMZ ... the rapper's been named as a suspect in an NYPD assault report, for an incident that went down around 1 AM Friday at the Boom Boom Room in the Standard Hotel.

We're told G-Eazy's party got into an altercation with a few other guys, and one of them claims a member of G's entourage hit him in the head with a glass bottle.
Our sources say the scuffle moved outside, where G-Eazy allegedly punched another man in the head.
